SIMPLE: black-letter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Black-letter
<hw>Black"-let`ter</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Written or
printed in black letter; <as>as, a <ex>black-letter</ex> manuscript or
book</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Given to the study of books in black letter; that
is, of old books; out of date.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Kemble, a <qex>black-letter</qex> man!</q> <rj><qau>J.
Boaden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the days in the calendar not
marked with red letters as saints' days; -- compare
<contr>red-letter</contr>.</def> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>Unlucky;
inauspicious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blacklist</ent>⟦br⟧
